text: Aksarovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Muraptalovsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 321 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 26 km from Yermolayevo, 11 km from Novomuraptalovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Aksarovo
